<TITLE> HC orders inclusion of SCF in war history petition </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com)The High Court has ordered inclusion of the Sector Commanders' Forum as an additional party in the writ petition filed challenging the validity of official documentation of liberation war of Bangladesh. On Thursday, the bench of justices ABM Khairul Haq and Md Momtaj Uddin Ahmed gave the order upon a petition of former army chief retired lieutenant general Harun-or-Rashid on behalf of the Forum, a platform of 1971 war commanders now fighting to put the perpetrators of war crimes on trial. The court also directed the government orally to produce any personal document of the former president major general Ziaur Rahman regarding proclamation of liberation war before the court on Wednesday. On May 13, the HC directed inclusion of M Hamidulla Khan Bir Pratik , commander of 11 sector of the liberation to be one of the parties in the petition. On Apr 20 , the court upon a writ petition filed by Dr. MA Suman , a freedom fighter, issued a rule upon the government to explain why it should not be asked to proscribe the impugned 2004 edition of the Bangladesh War of Independence mentioning Maj Ziaur Rahman as the 'proclaimer' of the independence on Mar 26 ,1971. b
